
[1]geometrical

   GEOMET'RICAL, a. [Gr.] Pertaining to geometry.

   1. According to the rules or principles of geometry; done by geometry.

   2. Disposed according to geometry.

     Geometrical progression, is when the terms increase or decrease by
                equal ratios; as 2.4.8.16.32. or 32.16.8.4.2.
